    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I agree with this.\r\nPersonally I prefer the first suggestion as long as `init` itself doesn't bring us much value.\r\nIf we can merge the usage of `init` and `render` into one `render` function, we can do in `render` what `init` used to do, for example, assigning variables using `helper`. And they will be done only once by using `isFirstRender`.",
